                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d805">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/9–1044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-10T00:00:00+03:06"
                            >September 10, 1944—12 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>274. Yesterday Jordan and I agreed to recommend to our Governments: (1)
                    Additional 7,000 tons of grain and therefore entire 50,000 tons grain supplied
                    in 1944 should be included in subsidy part of Joint Supply program, (2) reserve
                    stocks referred to in joint note to King (reDepts 149, July 26, 5 p.m.,
                    paragraph A) can be [<hi rend="italic">procured?</hi>] and held at Jidda in
                    warehouse supervised by MESC if Saudi Government wishes to have this done to
                    guarantee readiness of supplies and to give assurance against shipping delays.
                    If Saudi Government objects to MESC controlled warehouse for reserves whose
                    delivery is not yet due, stocks can be held elsewhere in Red Sea areas under
                    Allied control.</p>
                <p>Repeated Cairo for AEMME.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
